A lobby group representing a section of Imperial Bank depositors has started inviting potential investors to take up an equity stake at the troubled institution.This after the Central Bank of Kenya opened the expression of interest window last week, paving the way for potential investors to submit their bids or even propose other transaction structures for the bank that is currently under receivership.Investors eyeing to buy the distressed lender have until Friday September 29 to express their interest. Audit and consulting firm KPMG have been appointed as advisors for this process that is expected to be complete by at least February next year.Buoyed by this announcement, the lobby group, through their Facebook and Twitter accounts, are calling on banks to consider investing in Imperial Bank promising the potential investors immense expansion and growth opportunities.The group&acirc;&#128;&#153;s spokesman Mahmoud Khambiye told The Star the main objective is to try and drum up enthusiasm for the offer. &acirc;&#128;&#156;The bank was closed due to processes not liquid issues...there is great potential to revive this bank,&acirc;&#128;&#157; he explained. He said the lobby is in the process of drafting official letters to at least 10 potential investors. &acirc;&#128;&#156;Our main objective is that everybody gets back their funds,&acirc;&#128;&#157; he added. &acirc;&#128;&#156;We have targeted people who are near to us.&acirc;&#128;&#157;One of the appeals, by the group that has more than 4, 800 Facebook members and 950 followers on Twitter, to Dubai Islamic CEO said: &acirc;&#128;&#156;You&acirc;&#128;&#153;re invited...the Good Bank &acirc;&#128;&#156; IBL-IR with 28 branches is ready for your DIB Bank expansion in strategic locations countrywide. Over 4,500 depositors with funds in &acirc;&#128;&#156;BILLIONS&acirc;&#128;&#157; already in the bank means you instantly get 4,500 free marketing executives for your bank.&acirc;&#128;&#157;Other similar invitations were sent to CEOs of commercial banks such as NIC Bank, Kenya Commercial Bank, Mayfair Bank, SBM Group and to international lender Societe Generale. The French bank was last week given the go-ahead by the CBK to open a representative office in Kenya with unconfirmed reports indicating that it is eyeing a stake in the other troubled Kenyan lender Chase Bank. &acirc;&#128;&#156;Welcome to Kenya, @SocieteGenerale, we look forward to you looking into @ImperialBankLtd -IR and participating in the EOI process,&acirc;&#128;&#157; one of the tweets from the lobby group reads.Khambiye said similar appeals will be sent to international banks such as NetBank and Qatar Bank. According to information on its website, the lobby group was formed to provide a voice for the depositors of Imperial Bank so that they can be heard and be included in all the decision making to do with their bank. It says it stands for the 54, 000 depositors of the bank and consists of three lobby groups from the Coast region, Nairobi region and upcountry. &acirc;&#128;&#156;Your original plan to get established branches in a network and being a larger bank in an instant is now back on the table,&acirc;&#128;&#157; the message to Dubai Islamic Bank added. To Mayfair Bank chairman Anjay Patel, the invite read: &acirc;&#128;&#156;The Good Bank &acirc;&#128;&#156; of IBL- IR has 28 branches ready for your Mayfair Bank expansion in strategic locations countrywide, This will mean that you will raise from the back of the line to the top 20 bank in Kenya overnight.&acirc;&#128;&#157; It is not however clear whether any of the invited banks has heeded to the calls to participate in the expression of interest bid.